{
  "doc_id": "8441",
  "text": "Extenders contain nutritional and protective ingredients which are added to semen to preserve sperm fertilizing ability. Egg yolk is the most widely used extender component of mammalian sperm. Its role in protecting the frozen sperm is not fully clear however several researchers have suggested several mechanisms of action [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the addition of egg yolk contributes to great variability among batches of extender and increases the risk of disease transmission [CITATION_3] . Moreover, harmful metabolites and endotoxins could be contained in the egg yolk, that lead to negative effects on the viability of the sperm cells [CITATION_4] , egg yolk also contains steroid hormones that lead to the reduction of sperm motility [CITATION_5] .",
